    <name>Writing objectives: As easy as ABCD</name>
    <intro>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Instructional objectives must be &lt;i&gt;specific&lt;/i&gt;, &lt;i&gt;outcomes-based&lt;/i&gt;, and &lt;i&gt;measurable&lt;/i&gt;. &lt;b&gt;ABCD&lt;/b&gt; is a mnemonic for remembering these steps:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;A = Audience&lt;/b&gt;, the student for whom this objective is written&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;B = Behavior&lt;/b&gt;, the verb that describes what you want them to do&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;C = Condition&lt;/b&gt;, the circumstances under which they should do the action&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;D = Degree&lt;/b&gt;, the level of acceptable performance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Here are 2 examples:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Given an outline map of Africa [condition], pre-GED students [audience] will be able to identify and label the countries [behavior] with 90% accuracy [degree].&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Given a prompt [condition], students [audience] will write an introductory paragraph [behavior] that meets a rubric's "excellent" expectations [degree]. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Move beyond "students will learn to..." -- Grab one of &lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Taxonomy_of_Verbs_for_TEAL.pdf" title="PDF - opens in new window" target="_blank"&gt;these verbs&lt;/a&gt; for your objective and make your learning actionable. Download the pdf versionÂ of the lists, categorized for verbs that describe tasks, study skills, analysis skills, and synthesis skills. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Differentiate your objective &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;by amount of time allotted, level of support given, amount of text expected, and/or level of performance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;For this assignment, write a differentiated objective for your lesson plan to accommodate various groups.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
